VPC Endpoints:
==============


- Connect to AWS Services using a private network
- Access AWS Network within the private Network
- Scale Horizontally and Redundant
- No need IGW, NAT Gateway to access AWS Services
- Interface provisions an ENI (private IP address) as an entry point - most AWS Services
- Gateway provisions a target and must be updated in route table - S3 and DynamoDB
- DNS Setting Resolution
- Route Tables

- Default region of the AWS CLI is us-east-1
- Take a note of the region while using the AWS CLI
- S3 and DynamoDB are Gateway Setup
- Other services are interface Setup

